name: CommandNodeHelper
description: The CommandNodeHelper class is a wrapper around Minecraft's Brigadier command system that represents a command node in the command tree.
overview:
This class is primarily used internally for command registration and management operations, allowing users to temporarily unregister commands and re-register them later.

Command nodes are the fundamental building blocks of Minecraft's command system, representing individual commands, arguments, and literals in the command tree structure.

methods.name: getRaw
methods.description: Returns the underlying Brigadier CommandNode object.
examples:
const rawNode = commandNode.getRaw();
Chat.log(`Raw command node: ${rawNode.getClass().getName()}`);

methods.name: equals
methods.description: Compares this CommandNodeHelper to another object for equality.

methods.name: hashCode
methods.description: Returns the hash code of the underlying command node.
